00:13:10,834 --> 00:13:12,067
you guys going
camping, too?

266
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:14,434
Mother/daughter camp-out.

267
00:13:14,501 --> 00:13:16,467
These broads
drive me nuts.

268
00:13:16,534 --> 00:13:19,467
They can't go anywhere
without their hair-dryers.

269
00:13:19,534 --> 00:13:20,434
You know the type.

270
00:13:20,501 --> 00:13:22,367
Yeah.

271
00:13:22,434 --> 00:13:25,200
Jo and me--we brought
our rock-climbing gear,

272
00:13:25,267 --> 00:13:27,067
survival tents,
hiking boots.

273
00:13:27,067 --> 00:13:30,367
We'll do some exploring,
right, Jo?

274
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:31,767
Catch you later, bud.

275
00:13:31,834 --> 00:13:33,868
Take care.

276
00:13:35,067 --> 00:13:37,601
Hey, dad, the boat--
it's so cool.

277
00:13:37,667 --> 00:13:39,701
The trip
takes three hours.

278
00:13:39,767 --> 00:13:40,667
You're kidding.

279
00:13:40,734 --> 00:13:42,133
Want pizza?

280
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,200
No.
I just had some.

281
00:13:43,267 --> 00:13:44,434
[Horn blows]

282
00:13:44,501 --> 00:13:48,901
<i>Attention, please.</i>
<i>The</i> Catalina express...

283
00:13:48,968 --> 00:13:50,067
That's us.

284
00:13:50,067 --> 00:13:52,100
What did he say?

285
00:13:52,167 --> 00:13:54,234
Just tell them you're
in the fourth grade.

286
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,801
Michael, I could use
some help here.

287
00:13:56,868 --> 00:14:00,067
Thank you. Thanks.
Thank you, son.

288
00:14:00,133 --> 00:14:01,934
<i>Proceed to the loading dock.</i>

289
00:14:02,067 --> 00:14:04,334
Yeah, I got it.

290
00:14:05,334 --> 00:14:06,400
All right, campers.

291
00:14:06,467 --> 00:14:08,100
Just stack your gear

292
00:14:08,167 --> 00:14:10,334
neatly in the pile
inside the boat.

293
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:12,200
Now, I hope everyone

294
00:14:12,267 --> 00:14:13,868
remembered
to write their names

295
00:14:13,934 --> 00:14:15,267
on their sleeping bags.

296
00:14:15,334 --> 00:14:16,901
We're all friends here,

297
00:14:16,968 --> 00:14:20,634
but no sense setting the table
for temptation.

298
00:14:20,701 --> 00:14:22,133
Know what I mean?

299
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:25,100
Michael, you
could carry
something.

300
00:14:28,501 --> 00:14:30,234
I don't want to go.

301
00:14:30,300 --> 00:14:32,133
You were looking
forward to this.

302
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:35,334
I changed my mind.

303
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:38,400
Look, your mother
says we have to go,

304
00:14:38,467 --> 00:14:39,200
so we're going.

305
00:14:39,267 --> 00:14:41,100
Hike!

306
00:14:43,067 --> 00:14:43,901
Oh!

307
00:14:43,968 --> 00:14:45,934
Boy in the water!

308
00:14:46,067 --> 00:14:48,067
Just hang on
a second.

309
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:50,200
Boy in the water!

310
00:14:50,267 --> 00:14:53,133
[Blowing whistle]

311
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,968
Who is that kid?

312
00:14:55,067 --> 00:14:56,133
I'll pull you in.

313
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:58,901
This is no way
to start the weekend, son!

314
00:15:06,534 --> 00:15:08,234
This is
a good place.

315
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:10,400
Let's sit
by the window.

316
00:15:10,467 --> 00:15:11,701
The sun
will set soon--

317
00:15:11,767 --> 00:15:12,868
great time
to start

318
00:15:12,934 --> 00:15:16,367
a three-hour
boat trip.

319
00:15:16,434 --> 00:15:19,567
Hi. Mind if we buddy up
with you guys?

320
00:15:19,634 --> 00:15:22,067
Oh, gee,
that'd be perfect.

321
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:23,100
Great.

322
00:15:23,167 --> 00:15:24,801
[Horn blows]

323
00:15:24,868 --> 00:15:26,200
We're going to move!

324
00:15:26,267 --> 00:15:28,734
Brent, you're
going to lose--

325
00:15:32,801 --> 00:15:35,567
hi. I'm Aaron deutsch.

326
00:15:35,634 --> 00:15:37,534
Spenser Paley.

327
00:15:37,601 --> 00:15:39,701
You're the writer,
aren't you?

328
00:15:39,767 --> 00:15:41,868
Want to make
something of it?

329
00:15:41,934 --> 00:15:45,067
No. That's great.
You're doing
what you want.

330
00:15:45,067 --> 00:15:48,067
I'm a film editor--
well, I was.

331
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:49,734
I'm trying to move

332
00:15:49,801 --> 00:15:51,734
into commercial
real estate,

333
00:15:51,801 --> 00:15:53,334
which is crazy--

334
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:55,868
the economy
being what it is--

335
00:15:55,934 --> 00:15:58,534
but you got to pay
the bills.

336
00:15:58,601 --> 00:16:02,300
That's what life's
all about--

337
00:16:02,367 --> 00:16:03,567
trying to make
the best of things

338
00:16:03,634 --> 00:16:06,934
after you fail
at what you love.

339
00:16:08,968 --> 00:16:09,934
Michael, want to get

340
00:16:10,067 --> 00:16:10,968
something to eat,
son?

341
00:16:11,067 --> 00:16:13,067
Sure.

342
00:16:13,067 --> 00:16:14,400
Anybody catch
the Dodgers'
score?

343
00:16:14,467 --> 00:16:18,067
Not that I think
they won today.

344
00:16:18,067 --> 00:16:20,300
The line-up

345
00:16:20,367 --> 00:16:21,968
isn't hitting
worth anything.

346
00:16:22,067 --> 00:16:23,834
I'm hanging in
for football
season.

347
00:16:23,901 --> 00:16:24,901
Know
what I mean?

348
00:16:24,968 --> 00:16:28,100
Yeah. I'm going to get
some food. Excuse me.

349
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:32,100
Avoid the chili.
The burritos
are good.

350
00:16:32,167 --> 00:16:33,400
[Burp]

351
00:16:37,634 --> 00:16:40,067
Hi. Which are better--

352
00:16:40,067 --> 00:16:42,300
the ranch-style
salad-dressing
potato chips

353
00:16:42,367 --> 00:16:46,567
or the onion-soup-dip
flavored potato chips?

354
00:16:46,634 --> 00:16:49,501
You know what? I'll take one of
each and two root beers.

355
00:16:53,534 --> 00:16:55,100
Hi.

356
00:16:55,167 --> 00:16:56,767
I'm married.

357
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:13,400
[Bag rustling]

358
00:17:20,634 --> 00:17:22,400
I'm sorry.

359
00:17:31,501 --> 00:17:33,634
[Crunching loudly]

360
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:42,200
[Horn honking]

361
00:17:43,968 --> 00:17:46,634
We're here--Catalina island!

362
00:17:46,701 --> 00:17:48,067
Wake up, you sleepyheads!

363
00:17:48,133 --> 00:17:50,701
Grab your gear
and assemble on deck.

364
00:17:50,767 --> 00:17:53,767
The fun begins now.

365
00:17:53,834 --> 00:17:56,934
Come on, Michael.
We're here.

366
00:17:58,334 --> 00:18:00,467
The fun begins now.

367
00:18:04,834 --> 00:18:06,701
What time
is it?

368
00:18:06,767 --> 00:18:08,767
Oh, jeez, it's
almost midnight.

369
00:18:08,834 --> 00:18:12,267
It's crazy to keep
10-year-olds up
this late.

370
00:18:12,334 --> 00:18:14,267
We'll get to bed soon.

371
00:18:14,334 --> 00:18:16,133
Come on.

372
00:18:20,334 --> 00:18:22,400
There it is!

373
00:18:24,334 --> 00:18:27,133
Hey, watch
who you're pushing.

374
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,634
This is it?

375
00:18:28,701 --> 00:18:31,334
I feel like we're
landing in Vietnam.

376
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,767
You were in 'nam?

377
00:18:32,834 --> 00:18:36,968
No. It was all volunteer
by the time I came up.

378
00:18:37,067 --> 00:18:38,267
How about you?

379
00:18:38,334 --> 00:18:39,767
Marines.

380
00:18:39,834 --> 00:18:42,267
My father was
in desert storm.

381
00:18:42,334 --> 00:18:43,767
Wow. Great job.

382
00:18:43,834 --> 00:18:45,267
He's
a fire fighter

383
00:18:45,334 --> 00:18:46,767
and a paramedic.

384
00:18:46,834 --> 00:18:50,400
If I burst
into flames here,
I'll call you.

385
00:18:51,601 --> 00:18:53,334
Come on, chip.

386
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:55,801
Let's go get
our stuff.

387
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:01,267
Step out.

388
00:19:01,334 --> 00:19:02,968
You got everything?

389
00:19:03,067 --> 00:19:04,267
This is so neat.

390
00:19:04,334 --> 00:19:05,901
Where's
our flashlight, dad?

391
00:19:05,968 --> 00:19:08,067
Dump your gear
under the sign

392
00:19:08,133 --> 00:19:10,067
and wait at the end
of the road.

393
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:13,234
Dump your gear
under the sign

394
00:19:13,300 --> 00:19:16,434
and wait at the end
of the road.

395
00:19:16,501 --> 00:19:18,267
Dump your sign--
I mean gear--

396
00:19:18,334 --> 00:19:19,300
under the sign

397
00:19:19,367 --> 00:19:22,801
and wait at the end
of the road.

398
00:19:22,868 --> 00:19:24,968
Dump your sign--
whatever.

399
00:19:25,067 --> 00:19:26,868
[Blows whistle]

400
00:19:26,934 --> 00:19:29,133
Put your gear
under the sign

401
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:31,267
and gather on the road.

402
00:19:31,334 --> 00:19:33,067
Why?

403
00:19:33,067 --> 00:19:36,100
We're trying to stick
to a schedule, sir.

404
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:39,100
We'd all like
to get to bed soon.

405
00:19:39,167 --> 00:19:41,968
Where is the camp?
I can't see anything.

406
00:19:42,067 --> 00:19:43,067
[Horn honks]

407
00:19:43,133 --> 00:19:46,634
Let's bring that truck
down here now.

408
00:19:46,701 --> 00:19:48,767
Everyone,
get off the road.

409
00:19:48,834 --> 00:19:51,767
Watch out
for this drop-off here.

410
00:19:51,834 --> 00:19:53,400
Bring it down here.

411
00:19:53,467 --> 00:19:56,267
You having
a good time,
Michael?

412
00:19:56,334 --> 00:19:58,067
This is cool,
huh?

413
00:19:58,100 --> 00:19:59,267
Oh, yeah.

414
00:19:59,334 --> 00:20:01,100
Let's all pitch in

415
00:20:01,167 --> 00:20:04,234
and toss this gear
into the truck.

416
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:06,968
We just finished tossing it
on the ground.

417
00:20:07,033 --> 00:20:08,734
Do what he says.

418
00:20:08,801 --> 00:20:11,234
Sometimes, it's important
to question authority.

419
00:20:11,300 --> 00:20:12,634
But all the time?

420
00:20:12,701 --> 00:20:15,000
That's it.
Everybody
pitches in.

421
00:20:15,067 --> 00:20:16,400
Everybody helps.

422
00:20:16,467 --> 00:20:19,400
As soon as we get
the truck loaded,

423
00:20:19,467 --> 00:20:22,400
we can hike to the camp.

424
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,667
Hike?

425
00:20:24,734 --> 00:20:28,133
For those of you
on your first visit here,

426
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:29,501
the road gets narrow,

427
00:20:29,567 --> 00:20:32,434
especially where it winds
along the cliffs.

428
00:20:32,501 --> 00:20:34,334
This is insane.

429
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,734
Dad, be quiet!

430
00:20:35,801 --> 00:20:38,434
So make sure you all have
your flashlights.

431
00:20:38,501 --> 00:20:41,434
If we keep up a good pace,

432
00:20:41,501 --> 00:20:44,267
we should meet the truck
in the camp

433
00:20:44,334 --> 00:20:45,801
in, oh, 45 minutes.

434
00:20:45,868 --> 00:20:48,133
You'll have
all these kids

435
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:51,968
taking a hike
in the middle
of the night?

436
00:20:52,067 --> 00:20:53,267
Who's the wimp?

437
00:20:53,334 --> 00:20:54,767
Dad,
I'm not tired.

438
00:20:54,834 --> 00:20:56,400
Can't we take
the truck?

439
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:58,167
Because my arches--

440
00:20:58,234 --> 00:20:59,567
that's a good point.

441
00:20:59,634 --> 00:21:01,200
For insurance reasons,

442
00:21:01,267 --> 00:21:04,067
no one can ride
in the truck.

443
00:21:04,067 --> 00:21:07,200
But it's
o.K. To hike
in total darkness?

444
00:21:07,267 --> 00:21:09,534
Toss the wuss
back on the ferry!

445
00:21:09,601 --> 00:21:11,801
Dad, you're
embarrassing me.

446
00:21:11,868 --> 00:21:15,400
Don't worry.

447
00:21:15,467 --> 00:21:16,767
Why can't we
take a ride

448
00:21:16,834 --> 00:21:18,100
in those boats
over there?

449
00:21:18,167 --> 00:21:20,200
Sir, the water taxis

450
00:21:20,267 --> 00:21:22,701
are to take the girls
to their camp.

451
00:21:22,767 --> 00:21:24,934
Why is this idiot
in charge?

452
00:21:25,067 --> 00:21:26,734
You'd want to be?

453
00:21:28,267 --> 00:21:29,300
[Blows whistle]

454
00:21:29,367 --> 00:21:31,200
Take off, driver.

455
00:21:31,267 --> 00:21:32,701
If everybody's ready,

456
00:21:32,767 --> 00:21:34,901
let's light up
those flashlights

457
00:21:34,968 --> 00:21:36,200
and get marching--

458
00:21:36,267 --> 00:21:39,200
two by two,
quick time. Ho!

459
00:21:39,267 --> 00:21:41,067
[Blowing whistle]

460
00:21:42,968 --> 00:21:44,200
Come on!

461
00:21:44,267 --> 00:21:46,100
Check it out!

462
00:21:46,167 --> 00:21:48,200
It's
a 45-minute hike.

463
00:21:48,267 --> 00:21:50,701
The camp's
a couple miles away.

464
00:21:50,767 --> 00:21:53,567
What other choice
do we have?

465
00:22:05,234 --> 00:22:06,367
You know,

466
00:22:06,434 --> 00:22:09,200
$50 for all 4 of us
wasn't bad.

467
00:22:09,267 --> 00:22:11,567
Sir, I guess
you probably make

468
00:22:11,634 --> 00:22:14,567
a lot of money
doing this.

469
00:22:17,234 --> 00:22:20,067
The little guy
Peter out?

470
00:22:20,067 --> 00:22:22,067
My daddy
didn't want us--

471
00:22:22,133 --> 00:22:24,067
Michael,
try and relax, son.

472
00:22:24,133 --> 00:22:25,367
You're very,
very tired.

473
00:22:25,434 --> 00:22:27,367
Tomorrow morning,
nobody will remember

474
00:22:27,434 --> 00:22:30,200
that we didn't hike
over with them, o.K.?

475
00:22:30,267 --> 00:22:32,067
Just rest, my son.

476
00:22:37,067 --> 00:22:38,133
Careful.

477
00:22:39,267 --> 00:22:41,300
So this is it?

478
00:22:41,367 --> 00:22:44,367
We don't
have to walk
any further?

479
00:22:44,434 --> 00:22:46,567
Well, this is it--

480
00:22:46,634 --> 00:22:49,200
what there is
left of it.

481
00:22:49,267 --> 00:22:50,701
Thanks for
the ride.

482
00:22:50,767 --> 00:22:54,367
In case you want
to leave early,
call me.

483
00:22:54,434 --> 00:22:56,067
Thank you.

484
00:22:56,133 --> 00:22:57,400
Good night.

485
00:22:57,467 --> 00:23:00,734
I guess
all our problems
are over now.

486
00:23:04,100 --> 00:23:06,067
Can we go home now?

487
00:23:06,100 --> 00:23:08,667
Come on. Let's go, guys.

488
00:23:14,801 --> 00:23:16,067
Gee, it's dark.

489
00:23:16,100 --> 00:23:17,200
Ow!

490
00:23:17,267 --> 00:23:18,601
What happened?

491
00:23:18,667 --> 00:23:19,667
I stepped
on something.

492
00:23:19,734 --> 00:23:20,701
What?

493
00:23:20,767 --> 00:23:23,567
Do we want to know?

494
00:23:28,067 --> 00:23:29,968
Here's a tent.

495
00:23:30,067 --> 00:23:32,300
Now I know
what they did
with the equipment

496
00:23:32,367 --> 00:23:34,334
from the Spanish-
American war.

497
00:23:37,968 --> 00:23:39,534
Great. This must be

498
00:23:39,601 --> 00:23:41,200
the four-star
dining accommodations.

499
00:23:41,267 --> 00:23:42,901
Hey, there's
our stuff.

500
00:23:42,968 --> 00:23:44,200
There is a god.

501
00:23:44,267 --> 00:23:47,200
O.k., there it is.
There it is.

502
00:23:47,267 --> 00:23:48,601
Thanks.

503
00:23:50,968 --> 00:23:52,200
We're here first.

504
00:23:52,267 --> 00:23:54,901
We can pick
the best tent.

505
00:23:54,968 --> 00:23:56,200
They're
all the same.

506
00:23:56,267 --> 00:23:57,567
Oh.

507
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:01,834
So, what do you think?

508
00:24:01,901 --> 00:24:06,067
You know, maybe we should
look for a better one.

509
00:24:06,067 --> 00:24:07,567
Michael?

510
00:24:12,601 --> 00:24:14,901
I guess this one's fine.

511
00:24:17,167 --> 00:24:19,200
O.k.

512
00:24:19,267 --> 00:24:21,067
Aw.

513
00:24:22,267 --> 00:24:25,167
O.k., Michael.

514
00:24:40,067 --> 00:24:41,567
[Kiss]

515
00:25:21,067 --> 00:25:23,067
[Zipping up sleeping bag]

516
00:25:30,767 --> 00:25:33,901
I knew this was
going to happen.

517
00:25:33,968 --> 00:25:36,868
No. No, thank you.

518
00:25:36,934 --> 00:25:38,901
[Cough cough]

519
00:25:39,968 --> 00:25:41,567
Ahem.

520
00:25:56,133 --> 00:25:57,400
[Clunk]

521
00:26:06,968 --> 00:26:08,701
[Squeaking]

522
00:27:08,601 --> 00:27:10,901
Please don't let it
rain tonight.

523
00:27:17,267 --> 00:27:19,167
Michael?

524
00:27:22,601 --> 00:27:24,767
Michael, wake up.

525
00:27:30,968 --> 00:27:32,200
What?

526
00:27:32,267 --> 00:27:34,701
We lived
through the night.

527
00:27:34,767 --> 00:27:37,701
Come on.
Let's go hit
the showers.

528
00:27:37,767 --> 00:27:41,167
I smell like
a bait boat.

529
00:27:44,601 --> 00:27:46,767
Michael,
don't do that.

530
00:27:46,834 --> 00:27:48,901
You're not home.
Get up.

531
00:27:48,968 --> 00:27:51,267
Michael?

532
00:27:51,334 --> 00:27:53,067
Michael?

533
00:27:55,100 --> 00:27:57,067
There's only
one stall open.

534
00:27:57,100 --> 00:27:58,367
O.k.

535
00:27:58,434 --> 00:28:00,601
Watch it.
It's slippery.

536
00:28:04,968 --> 00:28:06,467
How you doing?

537
00:28:06,534 --> 00:28:08,534
Fabulous.
I'll bring my wife here

538
00:28:08,601 --> 00:28:10,400
for our anniversary.

539
00:28:11,801 --> 00:28:13,167
Funny guy.

540
00:28:13,234 --> 00:28:16,334
Keep your
flip-flops on,
all right?

541
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:17,901
O.k., dad.

542
00:28:24,133 --> 00:28:26,067
Turn it on
all the way.

543
00:28:26,100 --> 00:28:28,367
It's on all the way.

544
00:28:28,434 --> 00:28:30,167
You're kidding.

545
00:28:39,634 --> 00:28:43,067
I don't feel dirty.
You feel that dirty?

546
00:28:43,100 --> 00:28:44,100
No.

547
00:28:44,167 --> 00:28:45,167
Let's go.

548
00:28:47,968 --> 00:28:51,400
I don't know.
Probably pancakes
or something.

549
00:28:59,234 --> 00:29:01,667
It's been
about six hours.

550
00:29:01,734 --> 00:29:04,868
They were supposed
to serve breakfast
at 7:30.

551
00:29:04,934 --> 00:29:06,167
It's almost 8:00.

552
00:29:06,234 --> 00:29:08,667
You said nothing
would bother you.

553
00:29:08,734 --> 00:29:10,167
Anybody get
any sleep?

554
00:29:10,234 --> 00:29:11,868
Michael slept
pretty well.

555
00:29:11,934 --> 00:29:13,167
You snored.

556
00:29:13,234 --> 00:29:14,667
I slept?

557
00:29:14,734 --> 00:29:17,868
The cots are hard.
Our floor is wet.

558
00:29:17,934 --> 00:29:19,334
Don't be a wuss.

559
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:20,300
Stop that.

560
00:29:20,367 --> 00:29:21,367
He is.

561
00:29:21,434 --> 00:29:23,300
Fine.
Don't call him that.

562
00:29:23,367 --> 00:29:25,200
Crickets
in our tent

563
00:29:25,267 --> 00:29:26,534
drove me nuts.

564
00:29:26,601 --> 00:29:28,267
Good morning, men!

565
00:29:28,334 --> 00:29:29,868
Good morning.

566
00:29:29,934 --> 00:29:32,934
It's been a half-hour.
When do we eat?

567
00:29:33,067 --> 00:29:34,601
We're working on it.

568
00:29:34,667 --> 00:29:37,367
How do you
work on breakfast?

569
00:29:37,434 --> 00:29:41,167
Just burn some toast
and throw it at us.

570
00:29:41,234 --> 00:29:42,501
[Laughter]

571
00:29:42,567 --> 00:29:44,334
I'm sure
it'll be

572
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:46,367
just a few
minutes more.

573
00:29:46,434 --> 00:29:47,834
That's my gym teacher.

574
00:29:47,901 --> 00:29:51,300
I have him all year.
Don't make him hate me.

575
00:29:51,367 --> 00:29:54,667
I won't make
anybody hate you.
Just relax.

576
00:30:02,601 --> 00:30:04,400
Do you have
French toast?

577
00:30:04,467 --> 00:30:06,200
My son doesn't like
scrambled eggs.

578
00:30:06,267 --> 00:30:08,000
I like 'em.

579
00:30:08,067 --> 00:30:09,167
You never
eat them.

580
00:30:09,234 --> 00:30:10,667
I like 'em,
dad.

581
00:30:10,734 --> 00:30:13,868
If you could
do me a favor--

582
00:30:13,934 --> 00:30:15,167
here's 5 bucks.

583
00:30:15,234 --> 00:30:17,667
Fry my kid
a couple eggs.

584
00:30:17,734 --> 00:30:20,901
I can't touch anything
except this spoon.

585
00:30:22,033 --> 00:30:25,167
I see. Well,
you're doing
a fabulous job.

586
00:30:25,234 --> 00:30:26,968
I'll submit
your name

587
00:30:27,033 --> 00:30:29,968
to represent
my district
in congress.

588
00:30:30,033 --> 00:30:31,167
Ha ha.

589
00:30:31,234 --> 00:30:33,033
Ha ha.

590
00:30:39,734 --> 00:30:42,033
The coffee's
pretty good, huh?

591
00:30:43,934 --> 00:30:46,267
How was the water-taxi
ride, baby?

592
00:30:46,334 --> 00:30:49,434
You said no one
would remember.

593
00:30:49,501 --> 00:30:51,501
No more boat rides.

594
00:30:51,567 --> 00:30:53,501
We won't even take
the ferry back tomorrow.

595
00:30:53,567 --> 00:30:55,501
We'll swim
like dolphins.

596
00:30:55,567 --> 00:30:58,033
They ran out of food.

597
00:30:58,100 --> 00:30:59,868
They ran out of food?

598
00:30:59,934 --> 00:31:01,501
We got prunes
and tang.

599
00:31:01,567 --> 00:31:03,901
Don't combine
those two.

600
00:31:03,968 --> 00:31:05,534
It could cause
a nuclear reaction
inside your stomach.

601
00:31:07,067 --> 00:31:09,734
They got this food
where they got those tents.

602
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:13,801
They say make sure
you're prepared--

603
00:31:13,868 --> 00:31:15,801
to order a pizza.

604
00:31:20,167 --> 00:31:22,400
If you don't like it,
get out of here.

605
00:31:26,667 --> 00:31:28,501
I don't
think anybody
wants to leave.

606
00:31:28,567 --> 00:31:29,767
I do.

607
00:31:29,834 --> 00:31:32,200
We're just
joking around.

608
00:31:32,267 --> 00:31:34,467
Try that
at the firehouse.

609
00:31:34,534 --> 00:31:37,167
The food's pretty bad.

610
00:31:41,267 --> 00:31:43,901
Look, my kid
really looks forward

611
00:31:43,968 --> 00:31:45,701
to coming here every year.

612
00:31:45,767 --> 00:31:48,701
Now, I don't want it
ruined by girls

613
00:31:48,767 --> 00:31:51,200
who can't stand
a little inconvenience.

614
00:31:51,267 --> 00:31:53,200
Humor might
make the situation

615
00:31:53,267 --> 00:31:54,968
more fun
for everybody.

616
00:31:55,067 --> 00:31:56,701
It's a school camp-out.

617
00:31:56,767 --> 00:31:58,467
We're not retaking
Kuwait.

618
00:31:58,534 --> 00:32:00,234
You're knocking the war?

619
00:32:00,300 --> 00:32:02,534
No. No, not at all.

620
00:32:03,868 --> 00:32:07,767
Thank goodness
we got that emir
back on the throne.

621
00:32:11,100 --> 00:32:13,167
I'm going to watch you.

622
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:17,367
Thanks.

623
00:32:18,534 --> 00:32:21,434
If I do
anything funny,
take my picture.

624
00:32:23,901 --> 00:32:26,734
That guy
will kill
your dad.

625
00:32:40,801 --> 00:32:42,067
[Honks]

626
00:32:42,133 --> 00:32:43,467
Good morning.

627
00:32:43,534 --> 00:32:45,934
I'd like to make
a couple of announcements.

628
00:32:46,067 --> 00:32:49,968
♪ Announcements, announcements,
announcements ♪

629
00:32:50,067 --> 00:32:51,634
♪ what a heck of a way
to start the day ♪

630
00:32:51,701 --> 00:32:53,300
♪ announcements ♪

631
00:32:53,367 --> 00:32:56,501
♪ announcements,
announce-- ♪

632
00:32:56,567 --> 00:33:00,567
Oh, boy. You campers
really got me that time.

633
00:33:00,634 --> 00:33:04,567
I won't make that mistake again.

634
00:33:04,634 --> 00:33:09,534
I do have
just a few brief...Notices.

635
00:33:09,601 --> 00:33:12,334
Please don't throw stones
into the cove.

636
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:15,334
It took mother nature
millions of years

637
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:18,901
to wash all those stones
up on the beach.

638
00:33:18,968 --> 00:33:22,834
If each of us throws
six stones into the water,

639
00:33:22,901 --> 00:33:25,467
there'll be no stones
left there.

640
00:33:25,534 --> 00:33:28,934
And the world would
come completely
to an end.

641
00:33:31,567 --> 00:33:33,467
You'll get us
in trouble!

642
00:33:33,534 --> 00:33:34,501
Sorry.

643
00:33:34,567 --> 00:33:37,567
Also, campers,
the west drainage basin

644
00:33:37,634 --> 00:33:39,133
is now officially open

645
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:42,901
for volleyball
and, uh, other kinds of ball.

646
00:33:43,701 --> 00:33:45,467
That would be
the swamp.

647
00:33:45,934 --> 00:33:46,901
Dad!

648
00:33:46,968 --> 00:33:48,601
Sorry.

649
00:33:48,667 --> 00:33:50,934
Our first activity
this morning
is archery.

650
00:33:51,067 --> 00:33:54,801
We'll see you at the range
in 10 minutes.

651
00:33:54,868 --> 00:33:58,601
Did anyone find
those bows and arrows?

652
00:33:59,701 --> 00:34:02,934
Right. Well,
we'll stay on top of that.

653
00:34:03,067 --> 00:34:04,300
And finally,

654
00:34:04,367 --> 00:34:06,400
remember
that we are guests

655
00:34:06,467 --> 00:34:08,100
here at this camp,

656
00:34:08,167 --> 00:34:12,200
and...and what,
campers?

657
00:34:12,267 --> 00:34:14,801
Good campers
are good guests.

658
00:34:14,868 --> 00:34:18,067
Leave this camp
the way you found it.

659
00:34:18,133 --> 00:34:19,734
A toilet.

660
00:34:20,868 --> 00:34:22,067
Dad!

661
00:34:22,100 --> 00:34:23,601
Sorry again.

662
00:34:40,133 --> 00:34:41,434
Nice shot!

663
00:34:41,501 --> 00:34:43,734
Right in the middle!

664
00:34:45,734 --> 00:34:47,067
All right!

665
00:34:47,133 --> 00:34:48,567
Yeah.

666
00:34:48,634 --> 00:34:50,234
They have fancy bows.

667
00:34:50,300 --> 00:34:52,234
We got
this kid stuff.

668
00:34:52,300 --> 00:34:53,734
They brought
their own.

669
00:34:53,801 --> 00:34:56,234
Nobody said
we could do that.

670
00:34:56,300 --> 00:34:58,534
We would have brought
our own.

671
00:34:58,601 --> 00:35:01,434
We don't have
our own bows.

672
00:35:01,501 --> 00:35:04,167
But we could have
rented some.

673
00:35:04,234 --> 00:35:06,400
Have you done
this before?

674
00:35:06,467 --> 00:35:08,234
Sure. A couple times.

675
00:35:08,300 --> 00:35:09,968
What do I do?

676
00:35:10,067 --> 00:35:11,534
Watch me
carefully, o.K.?

677
00:35:11,601 --> 00:35:13,467
You simply
take the arrow

678
00:35:13,534 --> 00:35:16,100
and rest
the back of it

679
00:35:16,167 --> 00:35:18,100
on this little
doohickey thing

680
00:35:18,167 --> 00:35:19,934
here on the bow.

681
00:35:20,067 --> 00:35:21,501
Then you shoot,
right?

682
00:35:21,567 --> 00:35:25,734
No. Uh, Michael, you know what
the secret to archery is?

683
00:35:25,801 --> 00:35:27,234
It's mental preparation, o.K.?

684
00:35:27,300 --> 00:35:30,167
You have to really
just close your eyes

685
00:35:30,234 --> 00:35:33,100
and imagine the arrow
flying through the air

686
00:35:33,167 --> 00:35:34,434
and hitting the target.

687
00:35:34,501 --> 00:35:36,567
You look stupid.

688
00:35:36,634 --> 00:35:39,868
I may look stupid,
but I'm not really stupid.

689
00:35:39,934 --> 00:35:42,634
This is ancient
zen Buddhist philosophy.

690
00:35:42,701 --> 00:35:44,567
This will work. Just watch.

691
00:35:44,634 --> 00:35:47,634
I just draw back
on the arrow here,

692
00:35:47,701 --> 00:35:49,868
and my mind is at peace--

693
00:35:49,934 --> 00:35:52,601
it's better
if you're not talking--

694
00:35:52,667 --> 00:35:57,434
and then--
and then I just let go.

695
00:35:59,501 --> 00:36:01,334
The ancient zen masters

696
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:04,067
didn't care
if they hit the target

697
00:36:04,133 --> 00:36:07,067
if their mind
was at peace.

698
00:36:07,067 --> 00:36:08,534
Your turn? Sure.

699
00:36:08,601 --> 00:36:10,934
O.k., carefully
take an arrow.

700
00:36:11,067 --> 00:36:13,067
Put this up. O.K.

701
00:36:13,133 --> 00:36:14,901
Now, just clear your mind

702
00:36:14,968 --> 00:36:18,167
and let your thoughts
guide the arrow.

703
00:36:22,501 --> 00:36:25,501
All right!
Practically a bull's-eye.

704
00:36:31,934 --> 00:36:35,067
It's not him.
It's his equipment.

705
00:36:45,901 --> 00:36:48,834
They said we weren't
supposed to use the canoes

706
00:36:48,901 --> 00:36:51,100
unless somebody
was watching us.

707
00:36:51,167 --> 00:36:52,501
I'm watching us.

708
00:36:52,567 --> 00:36:54,834
Here,
grab an oar.

709
00:36:54,901 --> 00:36:56,234
It's a paddle, dad.

710
00:36:56,300 --> 00:36:58,067
Of course.
Turn around.

711
00:36:58,133 --> 00:36:59,934
I could have
been

712
00:37:00,067 --> 00:37:01,234
a championship
canoer

713
00:37:01,300 --> 00:37:03,734
if I had done it
more than once.

714
00:37:03,801 --> 00:37:04,801
All right.

715
00:37:04,868 --> 00:37:07,367
O.k.,
here we go.

716
00:37:12,834 --> 00:37:14,601
[Groaning]

717
00:37:16,667 --> 00:37:19,667
Um, dad, we're going
to hit the rocks.

718
00:37:19,734 --> 00:37:21,067
This isn't
working.

719
00:37:21,100 --> 00:37:23,467
I'm paddling hard.

720
00:37:23,534 --> 00:37:24,767
You're
doing great.

721
00:37:24,834 --> 00:37:27,400
You know
what the secret
to canoeing is?

722
00:37:27,467 --> 00:37:29,067
It's teamwork.

723
00:37:29,100 --> 00:37:31,067
We paddle on
opposite sides.

724
00:37:31,133 --> 00:37:32,801
That gets us
going straight.

725
00:37:32,868 --> 00:37:36,100
You got it.
There's a rock under us.

726
00:37:36,167 --> 00:37:38,067
Stay away
from the rocks.

727
00:37:38,133 --> 00:37:39,567
Away from
the rocks.

728
00:37:39,634 --> 00:37:41,067
Away from the rocks.

729
00:37:41,133 --> 00:37:42,567
Say it with me.

730
00:37:42,634 --> 00:37:45,100
Think zen--
think away
from rocks.

731
00:37:45,167 --> 00:37:46,567
Away from the rocks.

732
00:37:46,634 --> 00:37:48,634
Let the rock
hear you.

733
00:37:48,701 --> 00:37:50,567
Stay away from the rocks.

734
00:37:50,634 --> 00:37:52,100
O.k.,
here we go.

735
00:37:52,167 --> 00:37:54,767
Go! Go!

736
00:37:54,834 --> 00:37:56,067
Row!

737
00:37:56,133 --> 00:37:57,767
I'm rowing!

738
00:37:57,834 --> 00:37:58,968
Uh-oh!

739
00:37:59,067 --> 00:38:00,234
Don't worry.

740
00:38:00,300 --> 00:38:02,634
I did
this once--
in a dream.

741
00:38:02,701 --> 00:38:04,934
Get away
from that rock.

742
00:38:05,067 --> 00:38:07,234
I'll get us
out of this.

743
00:38:07,300 --> 00:38:08,934
Here we go.
Paddle.

744
00:38:09,067 --> 00:38:10,067
O.k.

745
00:38:10,133 --> 00:38:11,567
Paddle, son.

746
00:38:11,634 --> 00:38:13,067
I'm paddling.
Whoa!

747
00:38:13,133 --> 00:38:14,767
Don't worry about it.

748
00:38:14,834 --> 00:38:16,067
We're moving now.

749
00:38:16,133 --> 00:38:17,567
Here we go.

750
00:38:17,634 --> 00:38:19,567
I'll do
the other side.

751
00:38:19,634 --> 00:38:22,067
O.k. We know
how to do this.

752
00:38:22,133 --> 00:38:23,567
Excellent,
excellent.

753
00:38:23,634 --> 00:38:25,567
Try
the other side.

754
00:38:28,133 --> 00:38:29,868
Want to race?

755
00:38:29,934 --> 00:38:31,367
You're on!

756
00:38:31,434 --> 00:38:34,067
First one
to the buoy wins.

757
00:38:34,100 --> 00:38:35,167
Let's not race, dad.

758
00:38:35,234 --> 00:38:36,701
We have to, son.

759
00:38:36,767 --> 00:38:40,100
We don't want
them to think
we're wusses.

760
00:38:46,133 --> 00:38:48,767
O.k., let's
get going, boy.

761
00:38:48,834 --> 00:38:50,067
O.k.

762
00:38:50,133 --> 00:38:52,501
O.k.
Oh, very good.

763
00:38:53,834 --> 00:38:55,200
Come on!

764
00:38:55,267 --> 00:38:59,734
On your Mark,
get set, go!

765
00:38:59,801 --> 00:39:02,234
Michael, give it
all you got!

766
00:39:02,300 --> 00:39:04,067
I'm trying!

767
00:39:04,100 --> 00:39:05,767
You're
slowing us down.

768
00:39:05,834 --> 00:39:06,868
Sorry!

769
00:39:06,934 --> 00:39:10,067
You're getting it
all in my glasses!

770
00:39:10,100 --> 00:39:11,567
Put the paddle in.

771
00:39:11,634 --> 00:39:13,234
You're
holding us back.

772
00:39:13,300 --> 00:39:14,567
I'm sorry!

773
00:39:14,634 --> 00:39:16,067
You're
getting
me wet!

774
00:39:16,133 --> 00:39:17,234
Michael!

775
00:39:17,300 --> 00:39:19,400
Oh, man,
she's way ahead.

776
00:39:19,467 --> 00:39:21,100
You're getting me
soaked!

777
00:39:21,167 --> 00:39:23,734
Come on! We're not
going fishing!

778
00:39:23,801 --> 00:39:25,734
You're rocking
the boat, dad.

779
00:39:25,801 --> 00:39:27,934
I'm not rocking
the boat.

780
00:39:28,067 --> 00:39:29,734
We can't
let them win.

781
00:39:29,801 --> 00:39:32,934
Michael, you're
getting it all
over my glasses!

782
00:39:33,067 --> 00:39:34,067
Sorry!

783
00:39:34,133 --> 00:39:35,400
You've got to steer.

784
00:39:35,467 --> 00:39:37,400
You wanted
to do this!

785
00:39:37,467 --> 00:39:39,100
Think zen. Think--

786
00:39:39,167 --> 00:39:41,601
I'm coming up front
to steer.

787
00:39:41,667 --> 00:39:42,968
Uh, dad!

788
00:39:43,067 --> 00:39:44,801
You're rocking
the boat!

789
00:39:44,868 --> 00:39:46,767
Whoa!

790
00:39:46,834 --> 00:39:48,634
Oh! Oh!

791
00:39:48,701 --> 00:39:50,100
Michael?

792
00:39:50,167 --> 00:39:51,267
Dad!

793
00:39:51,334 --> 00:39:54,067
Oh, now we're
in trouble.

794
00:39:54,133 --> 00:39:55,934
Oh, no!

795
00:39:56,067 --> 00:39:57,868
Bail.

796
00:39:59,634 --> 00:40:03,067
I think we want
to go towards
shore, son.

797
00:40:03,133 --> 00:40:04,901
It's that way.

798
00:40:04,968 --> 00:40:06,234
Don't worry about it.

799
00:40:06,300 --> 00:40:07,934
You should
have worn

800
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:10,200
your life
jacket.

801
00:40:10,267 --> 00:40:12,467
I'm floating.
I got some buoyancy.

802
00:40:16,367 --> 00:40:18,567
I still think
