♪ so I lost my Clementine

1321
01:03:40,167 --> 01:03:43,501
♪ oh, my darlin',
oh, my darlin' ♪

1322
01:03:43,567 --> 01:03:46,801
♪ oh, my darlin' Clementine

1323
01:03:46,868 --> 01:03:50,501
♪ you are lost
and gone forever ♪

1324
01:03:50,567 --> 01:03:54,067
♪ dreadful sorry, Clementine ♪

1325
01:04:03,200 --> 01:04:05,334
That was nice, men.

1326
01:04:05,400 --> 01:04:09,267
Before the evening ends,
there are a few things

1327
01:04:09,334 --> 01:04:10,300
I'd like to say.

1328
01:04:10,367 --> 01:04:12,467
Boo!

1329
01:04:12,534 --> 01:04:14,501
Now, hold on a minute.

1330
01:04:14,567 --> 01:04:17,567
I always give a speech
at the campfire.

1331
01:04:17,634 --> 01:04:19,667
We're trying
to stop you.

1332
01:04:19,734 --> 01:04:22,200
Spenser should
give a speech.

1333
01:04:22,267 --> 01:04:24,100
At least
he's funny.

1334
01:04:24,167 --> 01:04:26,868
[Cheering]

1335
01:04:28,667 --> 01:04:31,467
Dad, just don't
embarrass me, o.K.?

1336
01:04:31,534 --> 01:04:33,467
When
have I ever--

1337
01:04:33,534 --> 01:04:36,167
o.k. I won't
embarrass you.

1338
01:04:36,234 --> 01:04:37,834
I promise.
O.K.

1339
01:04:37,901 --> 01:04:39,100
All right.

1340
01:04:39,167 --> 01:04:41,100
[Cheering]

1341
01:04:43,300 --> 01:04:44,534
That's
not necessary.

1342
01:04:44,601 --> 01:04:46,234
If you'll pardon me,

1343
01:04:46,300 --> 01:04:48,067
I know
what the problem is.

1344
01:04:48,100 --> 01:04:50,634
It's your uniform.

1345
01:04:50,701 --> 01:04:53,100
Did I spill
something on it?

1346
01:04:53,167 --> 01:04:55,601
No. If you'll
forgive me,

1347
01:04:55,667 --> 01:04:57,400
it separates you
from us.

1348
01:04:57,467 --> 01:05:00,100
We're relaxed,
sitting around
the campfire.

1349
01:05:00,167 --> 01:05:02,067
You look
like a cop.

1350
01:05:02,100 --> 01:05:03,634
What do you mean?

1351
01:05:03,701 --> 01:05:06,267
You need to be
a leader,

1352
01:05:06,334 --> 01:05:09,534
but you need
a relaxed image.
Right?

1353
01:05:09,601 --> 01:05:11,734
Yeah! Yeah!

1354
01:05:11,801 --> 01:05:13,934
What kind
of an image

1355
01:05:14,067 --> 01:05:15,234
would that be?

1356
01:05:15,300 --> 01:05:18,067
May I demonstrate
with your outfit?

1357
01:05:18,067 --> 01:05:19,300
Yes. Go ahead.

1358
01:05:19,367 --> 01:05:22,300
Let's hear it
for a good sport.

1359
01:05:22,367 --> 01:05:23,300
[Cheering]

1360
01:05:23,367 --> 01:05:25,300
Take off
your clothes.

1361
01:05:25,367 --> 01:05:27,300
No, no--
just your shirt.

1362
01:05:27,367 --> 01:05:29,067
Take off your shirt.

1363
01:05:29,067 --> 01:05:30,300
You're kidding.

1364
01:05:30,367 --> 01:05:32,367
Want him to do it?

1365
01:05:32,434 --> 01:05:34,267
Yeah! Yeah!

1366
01:05:34,334 --> 01:05:36,067
O.k. All right.

1367
01:05:36,100 --> 01:05:37,501
It's
a lovely shirt.

1368
01:05:37,567 --> 01:05:40,834
You have that
beautiful choker
with the medal--

1369
01:05:40,901 --> 01:05:42,734
I made that.

1370
01:05:42,801 --> 01:05:44,300
[Spenser]
That's fabulous.

1371
01:05:44,367 --> 01:05:46,501
No sweat stains.
You're impressive.

1372
01:05:46,567 --> 01:05:48,234
I never sweat.

1373
01:05:48,300 --> 01:05:50,367
Tom Jones impression.
Catch, ladies.

1374
01:05:50,434 --> 01:05:52,801
O.k. That looks
great.

1375
01:05:52,868 --> 01:05:55,067
Let's put
your suspenders
back on.

1376
01:05:55,100 --> 01:05:57,467
Let's go
all the way
over.

1377
01:05:57,534 --> 01:05:58,601
O.k. One more.

1378
01:05:58,667 --> 01:06:02,067
Here we go--
over again.

1379
01:06:02,133 --> 01:06:03,067
Isn't that fabulous?

1380
01:06:03,133 --> 01:06:04,367
Yeah!

1381
01:06:04,434 --> 01:06:06,367
That didn't hurt,
did it?

1382
01:06:06,434 --> 01:06:08,067
No.

1383
01:06:08,133 --> 01:06:09,367
And the final
finish.

1384
01:06:09,434 --> 01:06:11,267
Isn't that
more relaxed?

1385
01:06:11,334 --> 01:06:13,701
Yeah! Yeah!

1386
01:06:13,767 --> 01:06:16,200
[Spenser]
Should he
finish his speech?

1387
01:06:16,267 --> 01:06:17,434
Yeah! Yeah!

1388
01:06:17,501 --> 01:06:19,767
Thank you.

1389
01:06:19,834 --> 01:06:22,467
Excuse me.
Coming through.

1390
01:06:26,200 --> 01:06:28,634
Dad, he looks
like a jerk.

1391
01:06:28,701 --> 01:06:30,834
But did I
embarrass you?

1392
01:06:30,901 --> 01:06:32,133
No.

1393
01:06:32,200 --> 01:06:34,133
Then I kept
my promise.

1394
01:06:34,200 --> 01:06:36,267
[Scoutmaster]
I don't know. I...

1395
01:06:36,334 --> 01:06:39,567
I guess I just
wanted to say

1396
01:06:39,634 --> 01:06:42,901
that I know
that I will always...

1397
01:06:42,968 --> 01:06:45,100
Always remember
the camping trips

1398
01:06:45,167 --> 01:06:47,133
I took with my dad.

1399
01:06:47,200 --> 01:06:48,634
What was important

1400
01:06:48,701 --> 01:06:52,534
was that we did them
together.

1401
01:06:52,601 --> 01:06:54,100
That's what
these weekends

1402
01:06:54,167 --> 01:06:55,834
are about--

1403
01:06:55,901 --> 01:07:00,234
bringing fathers
and sons together.

1404
01:07:00,300 --> 01:07:03,133
And that's something that we
need to do once in a while.

1405
01:07:08,634 --> 01:07:11,100
Something
just hit me.

1406
01:07:11,167 --> 01:07:12,934
What?

1407
01:07:13,067 --> 01:07:14,901
I'm having
a really good time.

1408
01:07:14,968 --> 01:07:17,968
[Scoutmaster]
The games we've played--

1409
01:07:18,067 --> 01:07:19,868
those aren't
what matters here.

1410
01:07:19,934 --> 01:07:24,067
If you have gotten
to know each other

1411
01:07:24,100 --> 01:07:25,834
just a little bit better

1412
01:07:25,901 --> 01:07:29,634
and gotten just
a little bit closer,

1413
01:07:29,701 --> 01:07:31,467
then believe me,

1414
01:07:31,534 --> 01:07:35,067
this weekend
has been a success,

1415
01:07:35,133 --> 01:07:37,934
and you're all winners.

1416
01:07:38,067 --> 01:07:40,167
Now, in the morning,

1417
01:07:40,234 --> 01:07:41,734
we'll have
our treasure hunt

1418
01:07:41,801 --> 01:07:43,067
in the silver mine.

1419
01:07:43,100 --> 01:07:44,200
Aw, yeah.

1420
01:07:44,267 --> 01:07:45,501
That's awesome.

1421
01:07:45,567 --> 01:07:47,868
We're going
into the mine?

1422
01:07:47,934 --> 01:07:49,434
[Scoutmaster]
Yes, sir.

1423
01:07:49,501 --> 01:07:52,701
Thank you all,
and good night.

1424
01:07:58,634 --> 01:08:03,267
Dad, we don't have to
do the treasure hunt.

1425
01:08:03,334 --> 01:08:04,567
It's no big deal.

1426
01:08:04,634 --> 01:08:06,567
Let's not talk
about tomorrow.

1427
01:08:06,634 --> 01:08:09,934
This is one of
the best nights...

1428
01:08:11,968 --> 01:08:15,234
[Michael]
Aw, man.
What happened?

1429
01:08:15,300 --> 01:08:18,434
Maybe a bear
got in there.

1430
01:08:18,501 --> 01:08:20,367
There are
no bears here.

1431
01:08:20,434 --> 01:08:23,234
Maybe a cat.

1432
01:08:27,467 --> 01:08:29,868
I think I know
what happened.

1433
01:08:29,934 --> 01:08:32,400
It's just some
good-natured hazing.

1434
01:08:32,467 --> 01:08:34,400
We'll help you
clean up,

1435
01:08:34,467 --> 01:08:36,834
pitch your tent
back up.

1436
01:08:41,534 --> 01:08:43,100
Excuse me.

1437
01:08:43,167 --> 01:08:45,234
Dad, it's o.K.

1438
01:08:52,534 --> 01:08:55,801
Guess you thought
that was funny.

1439
01:08:55,868 --> 01:08:57,234
What do you mean?

1440
01:08:57,300 --> 01:08:59,067
You trashing my tent.

1441
01:08:59,100 --> 01:09:01,067
Oh, that.

1442
01:09:01,133 --> 01:09:02,300
It's a tradition
here.

1443
01:09:02,367 --> 01:09:03,400
First-time
visitors

1444
01:09:03,467 --> 01:09:05,400
get their tents
trashed.

1445
01:09:05,467 --> 01:09:07,334
I wouldn't take it
personally.

1446
01:09:07,400 --> 01:09:11,133
Look, if you
don't like me, that's fine,

1447
01:09:11,200 --> 01:09:13,267
but if you have
a problem,

1448
01:09:13,334 --> 01:09:15,801
don't be a coward
and go after my son.

1449
01:09:19,267 --> 01:09:20,767
Let's just
forget about it.

1450
01:09:20,834 --> 01:09:23,234
We've had
such a nice night.

1451
01:09:23,300 --> 01:09:25,834
Are you calling me
a coward?

1452
01:09:25,901 --> 01:09:27,467
Only a coward
would do that

1453
01:09:27,534 --> 01:09:30,334
to a kid.

1454
01:09:30,400 --> 01:09:32,200
Dad, come on,
don't...

1455
01:09:32,267 --> 01:09:34,400
Let's not
start anything here.

1456
01:09:38,868 --> 01:09:40,601
O.k. Michael,
let's go.

1457
01:09:42,067 --> 01:09:43,801
Are you running away?

1458
01:09:43,868 --> 01:09:45,200
Get out
of my way.

1459
01:09:48,801 --> 01:09:49,567
[Aaron]
Stop it!

1460
01:09:49,634 --> 01:09:51,267
Come on, guys.

1461
01:09:51,334 --> 01:09:52,968
[Michael]
Stop!

1462
01:09:53,067 --> 01:09:54,467
[Aaron]
Break it up.

1463
01:09:54,534 --> 01:09:57,067
Stop it!

1464
01:09:57,133 --> 01:09:58,667
[Scoutmaster]
All right, guys,

1465
01:09:58,734 --> 01:10:01,067
I'm not having
any of this.

1466
01:10:01,133 --> 01:10:02,767
Get up.

1467
01:10:02,834 --> 01:10:04,067
Get up.

1468
01:10:04,133 --> 01:10:06,133
Stop. Stop.
Stop!

1469
01:10:10,334 --> 01:10:11,868
[Scoutmaster]
All right, Mr. Paley,

1470
01:10:11,934 --> 01:10:13,601
let's go to first aid

1471
01:10:13,667 --> 01:10:15,701
and patch you up again.

1472
01:10:18,400 --> 01:10:19,534
I'm fine, Michael.

1473
01:10:23,501 --> 01:10:24,868
Michael!

1474
01:10:24,934 --> 01:10:26,667
[Aaron]
I'll go
after Michael.

1475
01:10:26,734 --> 01:10:27,901
Get your nose
fixed.

1476
01:10:27,968 --> 01:10:29,601
You're not
the first person
who's suggested that.

1477
01:10:33,100 --> 01:10:34,901
You know, Mr. Paley,

1478
01:10:34,968 --> 01:10:37,634
I'm starting to hope

1479
01:10:37,701 --> 01:10:40,300
that you don't
come back again next year

1480
01:10:40,367 --> 01:10:42,167
because this camp
can't afford

1481
01:10:42,234 --> 01:10:45,901
to take care of you
for another weekend.

1482
01:10:53,601 --> 01:10:56,267
Michael,
where were you?
I was worried.

1483
01:10:56,334 --> 01:10:59,734
I took a walk.

1484
01:10:59,801 --> 01:11:02,734
You want to go
canoeing tomorrow?

1485
01:11:02,801 --> 01:11:04,501
That last time was
a freak accident.

1486
01:11:04,567 --> 01:11:06,767
Forget it.

1487
01:11:06,834 --> 01:11:09,100
How about archery,
then?

1488
01:11:09,167 --> 01:11:11,367
We didn't really
focus on it before.

1489
01:11:11,434 --> 01:11:13,767
The zen thing
was fun.

1490
01:11:13,834 --> 01:11:15,934
I want to go home.

1491
01:11:17,133 --> 01:11:19,767
Why? We've still got
another day.

1492
01:11:19,834 --> 01:11:22,067
I want to go home!

1493
01:11:46,067 --> 01:11:49,100
En garde, dad.

1494
01:11:49,167 --> 01:11:52,067
Oh!

1495
01:12:04,334 --> 01:12:07,067
Hey, Michael...

1496
01:12:08,300 --> 01:12:12,067
Look,
I've been a jerk
this weekend.

1497
01:12:12,100 --> 01:12:14,067
I know that.

1498
01:12:14,067 --> 01:12:17,968
I'm not that good
at this dad stuff,

1499
01:12:18,067 --> 01:12:21,667
but if there's one thing
I've learned this weekend,

1500
01:12:21,734 --> 01:12:23,868
I've realized
it doesn't matter

1501
01:12:23,934 --> 01:12:26,701
what happened to me
as a kid.

1502
01:12:26,767 --> 01:12:30,400
I'm here to help you
become a man.

1503
01:12:31,567 --> 01:12:34,501
I'm scared that
if you and I

1504
01:12:34,567 --> 01:12:38,067
don't work this out
while you're still my boy,

1505
01:12:38,067 --> 01:12:41,067
one day you'll have to
come back here

1506
01:12:41,067 --> 01:12:43,767
or a place like this
by yourself.

1507
01:12:43,834 --> 01:12:48,067
Look, dad,
I don't want to
hear about it.

1508
01:12:48,067 --> 01:12:49,300
Listen to me.

1509
01:12:49,367 --> 01:12:51,067
You might not
understand

1510
01:12:51,067 --> 01:12:54,067
what I'm trying
to tell you,

1511
01:12:54,067 --> 01:12:56,067
but sorting
this stuff out

1512
01:12:56,067 --> 01:12:58,067
when you're
a grownup--

1513
01:12:58,067 --> 01:13:01,467
it's harder
than you can imagine.

1514
01:13:01,534 --> 01:13:04,100
I still want
to go home.

1515
01:13:04,167 --> 01:13:06,400
Look...

1516
01:13:06,467 --> 01:13:08,634
If I go
in the mine

1517
01:13:08,701 --> 01:13:10,601
and we look
for treasure,

1518
01:13:10,667 --> 01:13:12,434
will you finish
the weekend?

1519
01:13:12,501 --> 01:13:13,934
You'll just
faint again.

1520
01:13:14,067 --> 01:13:16,400
Then I'll sniff
my smelling salts

1521
01:13:16,467 --> 01:13:19,100
and pull myself
together.

1522
01:13:19,167 --> 01:13:21,534
I want us
to find that treasure.

1523
01:13:21,601 --> 01:13:23,133
You two going back?

1524
01:13:36,067 --> 01:13:37,801
O.k.

1525
01:13:39,234 --> 01:13:41,067
Thank you.

1526
01:13:44,167 --> 01:13:46,801
We've changed
our minds.

1527
01:13:46,868 --> 01:13:49,067
That will still be $3.00.

1528
01:13:52,601 --> 01:13:55,067
No problem.

1529
01:13:55,067 --> 01:13:56,868
Each.

1530
01:13:58,801 --> 01:14:02,067
All right,
here you go.

1531
01:14:02,067 --> 01:14:04,701
That's a good boy
you got.

1532
01:14:04,767 --> 01:14:06,367
You're lucky.

1533
01:14:09,801 --> 01:14:11,868
I know.

1534
01:14:11,934 --> 01:14:14,701
Just in case.

1535
01:14:14,767 --> 01:14:16,100
Thanks.

1536
01:14:16,167 --> 01:14:18,067
O.k., Michael,
let's go.

1537
01:14:20,067 --> 01:14:21,234
Michael?

1538
01:14:21,300 --> 01:14:24,067
Michael, you know,
you could help me.

1539
01:14:24,067 --> 01:14:26,067
You could help me
sometimes.

1540
01:14:26,067 --> 01:14:29,601
Just grab
a sleeping bag.

1541
01:14:49,968 --> 01:14:53,067
You have 30 minutes.

1542
01:14:53,100 --> 01:14:54,734
Watch out for bats.

1543
01:14:54,801 --> 01:14:57,200
May the best pair win.

1544
01:14:57,267 --> 01:14:59,300
[Tweet]

1545
01:14:59,367 --> 01:15:02,067
Let's go! Let's go!

1546
01:15:09,100 --> 01:15:10,801
Let's go!

1547
01:15:15,100 --> 01:15:17,067
I'm right
behind you,
buddy.

1548
01:15:18,167 --> 01:15:21,400
Aw, again.
Again.

1549
01:15:24,400 --> 01:15:26,067
Watch your head,
dad.

1550
01:15:30,334 --> 01:15:32,234
Are you o.K.?

1551
01:15:32,300 --> 01:15:35,067
Yeah, I'm fine,
Michael.

1552
01:15:35,133 --> 01:15:36,934
Should we
go back?

1553
01:15:37,067 --> 01:15:38,234
No.

1554
01:15:38,300 --> 01:15:42,367
No. Let's keep going.

1555
01:16:02,234 --> 01:16:03,868
Dad, look.

1556
01:16:03,934 --> 01:16:05,167
These boards
are loose.

1557
01:16:05,234 --> 01:16:08,534
They might be
holding this place up.

1558
01:16:11,734 --> 01:16:13,701
There's
another tunnel
in here.

1559
01:16:13,767 --> 01:16:16,400
Yeah. Let's
keep going,
o.K., Michael?

1560
01:16:16,467 --> 01:16:17,934
Somebody stuck
these here.

1561
01:16:18,067 --> 01:16:19,300
They're
not nailed.

1562
01:16:19,367 --> 01:16:20,801
Leave them alone.

1563
01:16:20,868 --> 01:16:24,434
The treasure's here.
These boards
are to fool us.

1564
01:16:24,501 --> 01:16:27,534
This isn't
a good idea.

1565
01:16:28,601 --> 01:16:29,834
Michael.

1566
01:16:29,901 --> 01:16:32,167
I'm positive.
Come on.

1567
01:16:32,234 --> 01:16:33,868
Come on, dad.

1568
01:16:33,934 --> 01:16:35,167
Michael!

1569
01:16:35,234 --> 01:16:37,167
Michael...

1570
01:16:37,234 --> 01:16:39,601
Michael!

1571
01:16:40,434 --> 01:16:42,834
Come on, dad.
Down here.

1572
01:16:42,901 --> 01:16:46,334
Michael,
maybe we should
be heading back.

1573
01:16:46,400 --> 01:16:48,634
I'm sure
it's down here.

1574
01:16:48,701 --> 01:16:50,601
Agh!

1575
01:16:50,667 --> 01:16:52,801
What's wrong?

1576
01:16:52,868 --> 01:16:54,300
Just a spider web.

